ExecStats.Name: Solara
ExecStats.Details: Solara is not patched, but detected by Hyperion's. The detection is silent, so actions will be logged.

ExecStats.Name: Ro-Astral
ExecStats.Details: Ro-Astral is detected, likely due to the monitoring of ModuleScripts.

ExecStats.Name: Wave / Wave Lite
ExecStats.Details: Released two months ago, now patched and inactive.

ExecStats.Name: Krampus
ExecStats.Details: Krampus is no longer operational.

ExecStats.Name: Prism
ExecStats.Details: Claimed to be undetected, with a 68% UNC (undetected score).

ExecStats.Name: Feather
ExecStats.Details: A copy-paste of Incognito, reported to be a Rat.

ExecStats.Name: Celery
ExecStats.Details: Demo has ended, and the executor is currently patched. The project appears to be inactive.

ExecStats.Name: CodeX
ExecStats.Details: Very long key system, uses core technology from Arceus X.

ExecStats.Name: Solaris
ExecStats.Details: Solaris is not a copy of Solara. It is currently patched, and the project may be inactive, reported to be a Rat in the late year.

ExecStats.Name: Nihon
ExecStats.Details: Nihon is making a comeback, with development in progress. Limited functionality (e.g., print statements) has been demonstrated by developers.

ExecStats.Name: Synergy
ExecStats.Details: Synergy is currently in development. It has 80-100% UNCS, with internal and external versions, pros, and cons. It has been demonstrated by developers.

ExecStats.Name: Synapse Z
ExecStats.Details: Synapse Z has a built-in decompiler, high UNCS, and identity-level but crashes frequently and has many vulnerabilities.

ExecStats.Name: Lunar
ExecStats.Details: Lunar is no longer operational and has been discontinued.

ExecStats.Name: Incognito
ExecStats.Details: Incognito is patched, and there have been reports that it might use the userâ€™s graphics card for crypto mining.

ExecStats.Name: Carbon
ExecStats.Details: Carbon is an unreleased project developed by the same team behind Incognito.

ExecStats.Name: Delta
ExecStats.Details: Delta has very good performance and a well-built reputation, but some users have reported losing Robux. If you want to use it safely, try it on an alt account with an emulator inside a VM.

ExecStats.Name: Domain
ExecStats.Details: Domain is a paid executor. Identity-Level 3 and has Low UNCS, previously known for being undetected in the early Hyperion 4.0.

ExecStats.Name: DX9WARE V2
ExecStats.Details: DX9WARE V2 is a paid external executor. A comeback of DX9WARE, previously detected by the earlier version Hyperion 4.0, around 1 to 2 months away from now, it has a giant script library and a custom Lua environment.

ExecStats.Name: Script-Ware
ExecStats.Details: Script-Ware was a popular executor before the Byfron era but has since been shut down.

ExecStats.Name: Electron
ExecStats.Details: Electron is a paid executor. It tends to get patched shortly after each release, and updates take several weeks. The project may be inactive.

ExecStats.Name: AeroExec
ExecStats.Details: AeroExec is a free executor with a 58% UNC score. It has not been released yet, and its API is detected.

ExecStats.Name: Moon Executor
ExecStats.Details: There is no concrete proof that Moon Executor is working, but it is mentioned here for reference.

ExecStats.Name: Arceus X
ExecStats.Details: Just like Vega X and Code X, it has an unnecessarily long key system, but except that this one has been reported to steal users' data since 2021. Be cautious when using!

ExecStats.Name: Vega X
ExecStats.Details: Vega X is owned by 1F0 and has partnered with Arceus X. It has a mid UNCS score.

ExecStats.Name: Cryptic
ExecStats.Details: Cryptic is a free, newly released exploit with a very high identity level and UNCS, safety is uncertain.

ExecStats.Name: Evon
ExecStats.Details: Evon, previously known for being a free PC executor, now an internal exec for Android Roblox.

ExecStats.Name: Nezur
ExecStats.Details: Nezur is a free, AI-based aimbot similar to Aimmy but close-sourced. Some users have reported it may contain a virus. It has been proven that this is an older version of Aimmy. The owner seems to have a shady background.

ExecStats.Name: Nexus Admin
ExecStats.Details: Nexus Admin is an executor that offers you free and lifetime packages. It has a high UNCS, and every LuaU script is executable, but it has very strict TOS.

ExecStats.Name: Fusion Softworks
ExecStats.Details: Fusion Softworks is an AI-Based Aimbot similar to Nezur and Aimmy. It has a well-designed GUI and offers a 48-hour key. The project has not yet been released.

ExecStats.Name: Aimmy
ExecStats.Details: Aimmy is a free, opensourced AI-Based Aimbot, the original source to Nezur. The newest version requires a high-end PC; otherwise, it will cause significant lags and jitters.
